  "texts": [
    "As mentioned above, this experiment is based on the ant foraging model implemented in the NetLogo library (see https:// ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/models/Ants).",
    "It takes place in a twodimensional foraging area consisting of designated food sources scattered throughout the environment and a central nest where the ants must return to deposit the food they collect.",
    "The environment is designed to mimic natural foraging conditions, where agents (ants) must navigate to find food and return it to the nest while interacting with environmental cues such as pheromone trails and nest scents; see Figure 2.",
    "• Agents: The simulation features stateless ants, each operating as an independent agent without memory of past actions.",
    "These ants rely entirely on real-time environmental inputs and LLM-generated prompts to determine their behaviors."
  ],
